.SH NAME
HTMLSourceElement.media \- HTMLSourceElement: media property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]media\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLSourceElement\f[R] interface is a string representing the
intended destination medium for the resource.
The value is a media query, which is a comma separated list of
media\-types, media\-features, and logical operators.
.PP
It reflects the \f[CR]media\f[R] attribute of the \f[CR]<source>\f[R]
element.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]source\f[R]
  id=\(dqel\(dq
  src=\(dqlargeVideo.mov\(dq
  type=\(dqvideo/quicktime\(dq
  media=\(dqscreen and (min\-width: 600px)\(dq />
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] el = document.getElementById(\(dqel\(dq);
console.log(el.media); \f[I]// Output: \(dqscreen and (min\-width: 600px)\(dq\f[R]
el.media = \(dq(min\-width: 800px)\(dq; \f[I]// Updates the media value\f[R]
.EE
